AUDIO: 'Now, this paper did cause quite a stir in the neuroscience community. Brain organoids can learn using dopamine or ordered or disordered signals. They think that order is pleasurable and disorder is uncomfortable. This along with their capacity to learn in a'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'biological sense led to researchers claiming sentience. But seeing as sentience is not really a well-defined thing and it\'s nearly impossible to prove that you have the capacity to have an experience, that was debated and'

