AUDIO: 'degrade. They are, after all, made of neurons, and neurons do really like to have something to do. They embody them using a closed-loop learning system. So, the brain organoids would have just random neural activity. That neural'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'activity would be recorded, decoded, and then information would be given back to them about what they\'re doing in the virtual world. Now, I know this is a pretty simple diagram, but this is actually pretty incredible. They have an odor field, so they drop the brain'

